snippet.textDisplay:
I don't listen much Coke Studio, but this my first time hearing a song with a really high tempo. So many instruments, but all making the song really so upbeat!
Plus the guy on the synth adding some fucking awesome effects. I mean, it's adding so much "color" to the song. Holy Shit!
Definitely, one of different songs from CS's song library, and still highly enjoyable.

I sing the cosmic song
I sing the tale of my heart 
I chant the primeval sound
I sing the tale of my heart
Singing my tale I rejoice,
Like a tree bathed in the rain.
Every fibre of my being resounds with bells
They say here comes the Ecstatic one
I sing the cosmic song
I sing the tale of my heart 
I sing the infinite resonance
I sing the tale of my heart
Dancing I roam every street,
Kissing the foreheads of all I meet
A bird resting on my shoulder
Carrying a river in my embrace
I sing the boundless chant
I sing the tale of my heart
The chant exudes melody
I seize the dance of creation
Eyes moist with a profusion of tears
I sing the cosmic song
I sing the tale of my heart
I chant the primeval sound
I sing the tale of my heart
ANHAD NAAD Bajaya ..

snippet.textDisplay: It is seriously funny that people take a dig at artists and collaborations disregarding the amount of effort they've put in to make / recreate / adapt a song. I read people posting about accent, relationships, critics giving their expert opinion's... Do u have the balls to do what Ram and Sona do?? They make NON COMMERCIAL music... Not looking to sell the album but just bring fresh sound for people who enjoy music in the true sense and not pass judgements. They make the music that makes them happy. If u don't like the music they make i pitty ur taste. U might as well use the X button on the top right of ur computer screens or the < button on ur Android device or the home button on ur iOS device. They didn't force u to watch the video.
